1707132</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"attr-left\">Features:</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"attr-right td-list-item\">TESTING SET - ToolTreaux&nbsp; testing set comes with bottles of testing solution and a testing stone; Specifically designed to indicate whether your precious metals are legitimate</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"attr-left\"></td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"attr-right td-list-item\">USE IN SMALL QUANTITIES - Test solutions work best in small quantities, so it’s recommended to use the silver testing solution in small amounts for each test; 2 included bottles should last for many tests</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"attr-left\"></td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"attr-right td-list-item\">VERSATILE TESTING KIT - Silver, gold, or platinum testing solution set with testing stone is ideal for jewelry makers and sellers, coin collectors and sellers, metalworking enthusiasts, and jewelry appraisers</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"attr-left\"></td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<td class=\"attr-right td-list-item\">SPECIFICATIONS - Set size: 2 to 26 pieces; Materials: solution, stone, plastic); Bottle size: 0.5oz each bottle; Stone size: 2.25” x 1.75”</td>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t\t\t</tbody>\n\t\t\t\t</table>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- /product-specs -->\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"col-md-6\">\n\t\t\t<h1>ToolTreaux Complete Gold Silver Platinum Testing Solution Kits with Stone</h1>\n\t\t\t<h2>MSRP <span class=\"msrp-strike\">29.99</span></h2>\n\t\t\t<p>If you need to test silver, gold, or platinum quality frequently, then you absolutely need a reliable set of acid-testing solutions to make sure you’re identifying the quality of your precious metals accurately. The ToolTreaux acid testing kit comes with bottles of testing acid solutions and a testing stone to identify the quality of your silver.</p><p>To test content and purity, scratch the item onto the test stone leaving a visible deposit, then place a small drop of the solution over top of deposit. Ensure gold testing stone has been thoroughly washed before completing any testing!</p><p>The Silver Quality solution is designed specifically to indicate whether your silver is high-quality or low-quality. A cream color indicates high quality, usually sterling; black color indicates coin quality, green color indicates high amounts of copper/poor quality; gold color indicates brass/silver plated item.</p><p> The Gold and Platinum solution is designed to specifically indicate whether your material is legitimate. If the gold is the same karat or higher, the solution will not affect the deposit; if the deposit is of a lower karat, the deposit will dissolve and eventually disappear\n\nTest solutions work best in small quantities, so it’s recommended to use the neutralizing solution in small amounts for each test. Since we’ve included 2 bottles, this amount should last through many tests. Please note that this testing solution is not used to differentiate between different types of silver (example: .999, .925, .80)\n\nThe silver testing kit with a testing stone is ideal for jewelry makers and sellers, coin collectors and sellers, and metalworking enthusiasts and appraisers alike! Each bottle contains .5 ounces of testing solution and the stone measures 2.25” x 1.75”.\n\nSAFETY NOTE: Acid Testing Solutions can be harmful to the skin. Please exercise the utmost caution when opening and using this product and method of testing! Proper protective eye wear and gloves are highly recommended, as the solution can burn unprotected skin. Read the label on the bottle and follow the included operational instructions.</p>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"d-flex d-flex-col grid-60 center text-center bg-grey\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"newsletter-header m-all-1rem all-caps\">Newsletter</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"grid-100\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>SUBSCRIBE for Early Access to Sales</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Up to 90% Off</p>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"grid-80 center\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"newsletter-link\" href=\"https://my.ebay.com/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?AcceptSavedSeller&amp;sellerid=dealsonlywebstore\" target=\"_blank\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"newsletter-btn all-caps\">Sign Up</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div><!-- /col-md-6 -->\n\t\t<br></div>",
    "short_description": "If you need to test silver quality frequently, then you absolutely need a reliable set of acid-testing solutions to make sure you’re identifying the quality of your silver accurately. The ToolTreaux acid testing kit comes with 2 bottles of silver testing acid solutions and a testing stone to identify the quality of your silver. This testing solution is designed specifically to indicate whether your silver is high-quality or low-quality. A cream color indicates high quality, usually sterling; black color indicates coin quality, green color indicates high amounts of copper/poor quality; gold color indicates brass/silver plated item.",
